Diagnosis.
Distinguished from other known mirine genera by the following combination of characters: generally reddish brown, elongate, parallel-sided body; moderate size (
6.3 mm
in total length); almost glabrous dorsum; shiny, polished head and pronotum; shallow, indistinct longitudinal sulcus on vertex; long labium exceeding apex of metacoxa and reaching abdominal sternum VI (
Fig. 11A
); distinctly elevated scutellum (
Fig. 11B
); dark spots or annulations at bases of tibial spines; unique micro-spines on apical metatibia (
Fig. 11D, E
); almost smooth margin of pygophore without sharp process at base of left paramere (
Fig. 11G
); and a single, lobal-sclerite at apex of endosoma (
Fig. 9H
).
